article.description: — Kameron Langley recorded 15 points and 10 assists as North Carolina A&T defeated Florida A&M 70-58 on Saturday.
article.headline: Langley leads NC A&T past Florida A&M 70-58
article.linkText: Langley leads NC A&T past Florida A&M 70-58
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Kameron Langley recorded 15 points and 10 assists as North Carolina A&T defeated Florida A&M 70-58 on Saturday. Tyrone Lyons added 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Aggies (7-9, 3-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who won their fourth straight game. Blake Harris had 11 points and Kwe Parker added 10 points. Jalen Speer had 17 points for the Rattlers (2-7, 1-1). MJ Randolph added 12 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists. Bryce Moragne had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
